'Punjab' (}}, ShahmukhÄ« Punjabi: ) , panj-Äb, "five waters": ), also spelled 'Panjab',is the most developed,
populous, and prosperous province of Pakistan with approximately 55% of the
country's total population. [http://www.globalsecurity.org/wmd/l-
ibrary/news/pakistan/2010/pakistan-100615-rferl01.htm The Growing Threat In
Pakistanâs Punjab ][http://www.islamonline.net/servlet/Satellite?c=Article_C&pagename-
=Zone-English-News/NWELayout&cid=1239889006387 ] Lahore has traditionally
been the capital of Punjab for a thousand years; it is Punjab's main cultural,
historical, administrative and economic center. [http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/world/pakistan/cantt-
lahore.htm Lahore Cantonment ] Historically,
the Punjab region has been the gateway to the South Asia for people from Greece,
Central Asia, Iran and Afghanistan and Vice-versa. [http://www.zum.de/whkmla/region/india/xwpunjab.html WHKMLA :
History of West Punjab ] Due to its strategic
location, it has been dominated by various empires and invading armies
throughout history, including the Indus Valley Civilization, Vedic civilization,
Persians, Mauryans, Greeks, Scythians, Kushans, Guptas, Arabs, Turks, Mongols,
Timurids, Mughals, Afghans, Sikhs and the British.
